[{"title": "Cowboy\u2019s first all-road electric bike is a gentle beast", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24105614/cowboy-cross-all-road-electric-bike-price-specs", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T23:01:00+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A menacing-looking Cowboy Cross e-bike sits on a wooden bridge that traverses a pond with tall grass surrounding it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cWYutoI9MWwRVPxqFI-bdHxEoMs=/0x168:4032x2856/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73219260/IMG_2961.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Cowboy Cross in \u201cmushroom\u201d with the inverted front suspension fork clearly visible.</em> | Photo by Thomas Ricker / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"HC3Ipw\">Cowboy \u2014 the independent and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/7/21/23801720/cowboy-profit-next-vanmoof-bankrupt\">financially healthy</a> maker of sophisticated and highly advanced e-bikes \u2014 just took the wraps off its first all-roader that lets riders more easily escape cobblestoned city streets for greener pastures.</p>\n<p id=\"EX6VRo\">To do that, <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fcowboy.com&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sr"}, {"title": "Meta just showed off Threads\u2019 fediverse integration for the very first time", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24106231/threads-fediverse-demo-meta-fediforum", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T22:34:00+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing the Threads logo\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/TIXrC-kvxcH_rN5WTt7zMrSVrvQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73219222/STK156_Instagram_threads_1.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"0q72oH\">Threads is coming to the fediverse \u2014 and we just got our first official look at how that might work from Meta itself. During the FediForum conference on Tuesday, Meta\u2019s Peter Cottle <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XGEVy-CjBBg\">showed off a brief demo</a> of how users will eventually be able to connect their accounts and posts to the fediverse. The integration will let users share their posts across different platforms through Threads, letting them reach multiple audiences at once. Meta is just one of the many platforms <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24063290/fediverse-explained-activitypub-social-media-open-protocol\">aiming to join the fediver"}, {"title": "The Google Pixel 8A may get a brighter, 120Hz display", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24106211/google-pixel-8a-120-hz-brighter-display-displayport", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T22:23:47+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A render, supposedly of the Pixel 8A, front and back.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/SI86oBKUol6QrYeuOyZygDYMIM0=/200x0:2360x1440/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73219194/Google_Pixel_8a_5K_renders_Smartprix_Exclusive_1_scaled.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: <a class=\"ql-link\" href=\"https://www.smartprix.com/bytes/google-pixel-8a-exclusive-first-look/\" target=\"_blank\">OnLeaks / Smartprix</a></figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"iziv0z\">Google\u2019s Pixel 8A may have a 120Hz display \u2014 up from 90Hz in the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23716677/google-pixel-7a-review-screen-camera-battery\">Pixel 7A</a> \u2014 and a brighter screen, according to Kamila Wojciechowska, whose past leaks have included videos of the <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/4/21/23693598/pixel-fold-irl-video-leak\">pre-release Pixel Fold</a>. </p>\n<p id=\"kZdN3d\">Google\u2019s I/O 2024 conference is <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/14/24101171/google-i"}, {"title": "TikTok\u2019s podcast boom might be a bust", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24106175/tiktok-ban-podcast-planet-money-everything-everywhere-instagram", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T21:00:00+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of the Capitol building under the TikTok logo with a slash through it.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/37Q7QqpU6Bp5sfx5hcaBHde9c4o=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218949/STK051_TIKTOKBAN_CVirginia_C.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"hUDBQF\"><em>This is </em>Hot Pod<em>, </em>The Verge<em>\u2019s newsletter about podcasting and the audio industry. Sign up </em><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/pages/hot-pod-podcast-audio-newsletter\"><em>here</em></a><em> for more.</em></p>\n<hr class=\"p-entry-hr\" id=\"lBqZy7\" />\n<p id=\"d6lGnX\">The common wisdom goes that video is the key to podcast discovery: you take the juiciest clips from your show, hope one goes viral every now and then on TikTok, and then that wider (and younger) audience becomes your new listeners. <a href=\"https://www.tiktok.com/@spotify/video/706283216591"}, {"title": "Overwatch 2 unlocks all of its heroes", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24106082/overwatch-2-unlocks-all-of-its-heroes", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T20:55:40+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Screenshot of several Overwatch characters posing (Sojourn, Lifeweaver, Mauga, Illari, and Echo)\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/-WlTXFC2ZI7PKSWEc5r5LLhXHZc=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218935/videoframe_62079.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Some of the heroes added to Overwatch</em> | Image: Blizzard</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"EWsmWj\"><em>Overwatch 2 h</em>eroes will no longer need to be unlocked through Battle Pass or via purchase, taking some of the grind out of the now free-to-play team FPS. <a href=\"https://overwatch.blizzard.com/en-us/news/24062312/developer-update-hero-releases-mythics-and-gameplay-updates/\">Starting in Season 10</a>, players will be able to <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=H998wgSQm3M\">unlock all existing and future heroes</a> for free. This will include Venture, the <a href=\"https://www.polygon.com/23948665/overwatch-2-venture-season-10-hero-blizzcon\">latest "}, {"title": "Segway brings a sub-$1,000 smart robot mower to the US", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105936/segway-navimow-i-robot-mower-price-release-date-specs", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T20:29:26+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A robot lawnmower on a lawn with a lady sitting in a chair on her computer.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/2msoP9tOtvrBv4rU7jzHkh_F6lE=/0x0:8256x5504/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218838/Segway_Amazon_Image_1.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Segway\u2019s new Navimow i robot lawn mower is now available in the US on Amazon.</em> | Image: Segway</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"BiR6wo\">Following its launch in Europe earlier this month, <a href=\"https://navimow.segway.com/us/product/navimow-i.html\">Segway\u2019s Navimow i series robot lawn mower</a> is now available in the US. As one of the first robotic mowers under $1,000 that can navigate autonomously without a boundary wire, its arrival could be the beginning of the robot lawn mower going mainstream.</p>\n<p id=\"556Ojf\">The Navimow i series has two models: <a href=\"https://us.navimow.com/products/navimow-i-series-robot-mower-for-1-8-and-1-4-acre\">the i105N costs $999</a> and "}, {"title": "Google DeepMind co-founder joins Microsoft as CEO of its new AI division", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105900/google-deepmind-microsoft-mustafa-suleyman-ai-ceo", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T17:09:23+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo showing Mustafa Suleyman during the World Economic Forum 2024\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/ZHcNUa7viU2CbSVOXDIGTg_rrWk=/0x0:5736x3824/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218234/1935722537.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Getty</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"5yKDmB\">Microsoft <a href=\"https://blogs.microsoft.com/blog/2024/03/19/mustafa-suleyman-deepmind-and-inflection-co-founder-joins-microsoft-to-lead-copilot/\">has hired Google DeepMind</a> co-founder Mustafa Suleyman. In <a href=\"https://twitter.com/mustafasuleyman/status/1770123596121432351?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw%7Ctwcamp%5Etweetembed%7Ctwterm%5E1770123596121432351%7Ctwgr%5E%7Ctwcon%5Es1_&amp;ref_url=about%3Asrcdoc\">a post on X</a>, Suleyman announced that he\u2019s joining Microsoft as the CEO of a new team that handles the company\u2019s consumer-facing AI products, including Copilot, Bing, and Edge.</p>\n<p id=\"T8ID9l\">Suleyman will also serve as executive vice pres"}, {"title": "How AI companies are reckoning with elections", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24098381/ai-chatbots-election-misinformation-chatgpt-gemini-copilot-bing-claude", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T17:00:00+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Graphic photo illustration of I Voted stickers.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/vNsv8rpE_ajcQyNaTrZqlprIrNI=/20x0:2021x1334/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218198/STK466_ELECTION_2024_CVirginia_D.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Photos from Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Bnhjre\">The US is heading into its first presidential election since generative AI tools have gone mainstream. And the companies offering these tools \u2014 like Google, OpenAI, and Microsoft \u2014 have each made announcements about how they plan to handle the months leading up to it.</p>\n<p id=\"66cAt4\">This election season, we\u2019ve already seen <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/6/8/23753626/deepfake-political-attack-ad-ron-desantis-donald-trump-anthony-fauci\">AI-generated images in ads</a> and <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/6/24063885/biden-robocalls-ai-fcc-cease-desist-lingo-telecom-life-new-hampshire\">attem"}, {"title": "Lego\u2019s 3,745-piece D&D set comes with its own playable adventure", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105862/lego-dungeons-and-dragons-pictures-price-release-date", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T16:40:10+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"The Lego D&amp;amp;D Red Dragons tale set.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5KWRrW_cnPvgv7mKQppU-mA6YGE=/0x0:1500x1000/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218116/dungeons_and_dragons_lego_2.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Lego\u2019s Dungeons and Dragons set is ready to roll.</em> | Image: Lego</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"zpampw\">Grab your dice and get ready to (literally) assemble your adventuring party next month \u2014 Lego has finally unveiled the <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lego.com%2Fen-us%2Fproduct%2Fdungeons-dragons-red-dragon-s-tale-21348&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F3%2F19%2F24105862%2Flego-dungeons-and-dragons-pictures-price-release-date\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">3,745-piece <em>Dungeons &amp; Dragons</em> set</a> it co-developed with Wizards of the Coast as the tabletop roleplaying gam"}, {"title": "Hackintosh enthusiasts worry that the end is near", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105829/hackintosh-almost-dead-macos-sonoma-drivers", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T16:16:31+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of PC components used to create a \u201cHackintosh.\u201d\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/FoJ1jJ_MdxsVSAI1gCgwr72Rxpg=/0x13:3384x2269/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73218018/hackintosh.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Aleksandar Vaci\u0107</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"IqnJim\">For years, there\u2019s been a dedicated community of tech tinkerers who\u2019ve built unofficial \u201cMacs\u201d out of PC hardware or successfully <a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/hackintosh/comments/1bhl521/sucess/\">gotten macOS running on a laptop</a> that ran Windows in a past life. But now, some of those enthusiasts believe the Hackintosh dream is becoming more and more untenable.</p>\n<p id=\"8ZS1FX\"><a href=\"https://aplus.rs/2024/hackintosh-almost-dead/\">This blog post</a> by Aleksandar Vaci\u0107, <a href=\"https://9to5mac.com/2024/03/19/the-end-of-the-hackintosh/\">highlighted by <em>9to5Mac</em></a>, runs through some of the difficulties that seem to be growing b"}, {"title": "Ubisoft let me actually speak with its new AI-powered video game NPCs", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105748/nvidia-neo-npc-prototypes-gdc-2024", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T16:00:30+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/tRkouBkZTPK6IiLQY1X-AVk914Q=/0x113:2700x1913/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73217972/ubisoft_neo_npc.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>\u201cPassion. You can feel it, can\u2019t you?\u201d begins Bloom, an AI NPC from Ubisoft in collab with InWorld, and Nvidia.</em> | Photo by Sean Hollister / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"GnoGlY\">For the past three months, ever since <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24031687/nvidia-ai-npcs-convai-ces-2023\">I spoke to the AI NPCs in Nvidia\u2019s cyberpunk ramen shop</a>, I\u2019ve been wondering: Which game developer will take a flying leap on this controversial and intriguing tech? If you said \u201cUbisoft,\u201d the company that\u2019s always raising its hand to play <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/2/8/24066424/ubisoft-wont-increase-vr-investment-after-assassins-creed-disappointment\">with VR</a>, <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2022/4/6/23013346/ubisoft-ghost-recon-br"}, {"title": "The EV revolution hinges on upcoming emissions rule", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105752/epa-emission-rule-electric-vehicle-transition-timeline", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T15:56:10+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"President Biden on stage with EVs\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XGehDE2MHUbEfDyoqnSnTL-_fYc=/0x0:8256x5504/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73217925/1243229536.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by MANDEL NGAN/AFP via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"mCjXTP\">The speed in which automakers will have to phase out their gas-powered vehicles in favor of ones that are all-electric will be determined Wednesday, when the Environmental Protection Agency (EPA) is expected to release its new vehicle emissions rules. </p>\n<p id=\"p6I1xK\">Environmental groups are hoping for a sped-up timeline that will put the country on the path to an all-electric fleet by the early part of next decade, while automakers are pushing for a slower adoption that allows the industry to meet consumers\u2019 needs. </p>\n<p id=\"BPoBvq\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/4/12/23680204/epa-ev-tailpiple-emission-standard-climate-change-cars\">First "}, {"title": "The Acolyte\u2019s first trailer teases a deadly disturbance in the Force", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24105666/star-wars-the-acolyte-trailer-premiere-date-disney-plus", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T15:53:13+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": 