figcaption><em>The Covert Protocol demo shows how AI is being used to create unique NPC interactions.</em> | Image: Nvidia</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"MmJBrE\">Nvidia is showing off how developers have started using its AI \u201cdigital human\u201d tools to voice, animate, and generate dialogue for video game characters. At the Game Developers Conference on Monday, the company <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nvidia.com%2Fen-us%2Fgeforce%2Fnews%2Fnvidia-ace-gdc-gtc-2024-ai-character-game-and-app-demo-videos%2F&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2024%2F3%2F19%2F24105681%2Fnvidia-ai-ace-video-game-character-npc-covert-protocol\""}, {"title": "Google has a new head of Search \u2014 and she\u2019s all in on AI", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24105705/google-liz-reid-search-ai-sge-gemini", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T15:15:52+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Image of the Google \u201cG\u201d logo on a blue, black, and purple background.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/wHgCE_kibUyZb7XDlzhvHcdVk7I=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73217844/STK093_Google_03.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"JWETFC\">There are few bigger jobs at Google than being the person who runs Search. As of today, there\u2019s a new person in that seat: Liz Reid, who has been at Google for more than 20 years and has most recently been leading the company\u2019s efforts with AI search, known as <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/5/12/23720396/google-search-generative-experience-blue-links\">Search Generative Experience</a> (SGE).</p>\n<p id=\"BdZGLJ\">Reid\u2019s promotion is part of a bigger change within Google\u2019s Search team. Pandu Nayak, a longtime executive overseeing ranking and quality, is now going to be chief scientist of Search. He\u2019ll be replaced by Cheenu Ven"}, {"title": "Indie, rocked", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24070565/pitchfork-gq-conde-nast-music-industry-change", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T14:00:00+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"3D illustration of a volume knob with the Pitchfork logo being turned down.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/G0ikGA2Qv88Scf9PACljccjtCoY=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73217607/246985_Pitchfork_Decline_STILL_CVirginia0.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Cath Virginia / The Verge | Assets from Turbosquid</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Pitchfork exploded as the music industry changed, then was cut down to size by another wave of technological change.\u00a0Was that it?</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/24070565/pitchfork-gq-conde-nast-music-industry-change\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>"}, {"title": "DoorDash, Uber Eats \u2014 and Tony", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/24105686/doordash-uber-eats-delivery-apps-issues-rivian-history-vergecast", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T13:49:28+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A photo of a delivery man styled to match The Vergecast.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/XwucwydTANem2JRQZ0Ed-1qjcIA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/73217581/VST_0319_SitePost.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Alex Parkin / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"W3VuyC\">Delivery apps seem like a good idea, and it\u2019s obvious why they\u2019re handy to have around. It\u2019s also often unclear whether delivery apps actually work for anyone involved. They make your stuff more expensive, often in hard-to-see ways. They take huge fees from restaurants that need it to survive. Drivers don\u2019t get the pay or benefits they should. And in many cases, even the apps themselves don\u2019t make any money! What are we doing here? </p>\n<p id=\"iFyFJe\">Into that messy equation comes <a href=\"https://seattle.eater.com/2024/2/21/24079162/tony-delivers-seattle-delivery-app-fees-downtown\">a man named Tony Delivers</a>. Tony Illes has becom"}, {"title": "Anker\u2019s speedy Qi2 MagSafe chargers have dropped to new all-time low prices", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2024/3/19/24104781/anker-maggo-power-bank-google-pixel-tablet-amazon-echo-buds-deal-sale", "thumbnail": null, "date_published": "2024-03-19T13:37:51+00:00", "dead": false, "artist": null, "page_rating": 94, "comments": [], "language": "en", "page_rating_visits": 0, "source_obj__id": 359, "page_rating_contents": 94, "vote": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "permanent": false, "age": null, "tags": [], "bookmarked": false, "user": null, "source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "album": "", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Three grey-and-white Anker chargers on a bamboo desktop.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/